.Dd March 7, 2026
.Dt MD 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm md
.Nd query and transform Markdown files
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar program
.Op Fl -json
.Op Fl -dir Ar directory
.Op Fl i
.Op Ar file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
evaluates a jq-inspired DSL program against a Markdown file.
It parses Markdown leniently, preferring best-effort results over strict errors.
.Pp
If no
.Ar file
is given,
.Nm
reads from standard input.
.Pp
Plain text output is the default.
Use
.Fl -json
for structured output.
.Sh DSL
The DSL uses pipelines to chain operations.
Each stage receives the output of the previous stage.
.Ss Extractors
Extractors pull structured data from the document:
.Bl -tag -width "frontmatter" -compact
.It Ic frontmatter
YAML or TOML frontmatter as a record.
.It Ic body
Document body without frontmatter.
.It Ic headings
Headings with depth, text, and line number.
.It Ic links
Links with kind, target, text, and line number.
Kinds: standard, wikilink, image, embed.
.It Ic tags
Inline tags with name and line number.
.It Ic codeblocks
Code blocks with language, content, start/end lines.
.It Ic stats
Word and line counts.
.It Ic comments
HTML and Obsidian comments with kind, text, and line.
.It Ic footnotes
Footnote definitions with label, text, and line.
.It Ic nodes
Block-level document nodes with type, text, and line.
Types: heading, paragraph, codeblock, comment, footnote.
Type-specific fields: depth, language, kind, label.
.It Ic incoming
Files linking to the input file. Requires
.Fl -dir
or a file argument.
Returns source path, link kind, and line.
.El
.Ss Field Access
Use
.Li .field
to access record fields. Nested access:
.Li .author.name .
.Ss Filtering
.Ic select(predicate)
filters arrays.
Predicates support comparisons
.Pq Li "==, !=, <, >, <=, >=" ,
boolean logic
.Pq Li "and, or, not" ,
and string functions
.Pq Li "contains(), startswith()" .
.Pp
.Ic skip_until(predicate)
drops array elements until the predicate matches (exclusive of the match).
.Ic take_until(predicate)
takes array elements until the predicate matches (exclusive of the match).
These compose for positional queries on
.Ic nodes .
.Ss List Operations
.Bl -tag -width "group(.field)" -compact
.It Ic first
First element.
.It Ic last
Last element.
.It Ic count
Length of an array, string, or record.
.It Ic reverse
Reverse order.
.It Ic map(.field)
Extract a field from each element.
.It Ic unique
Deduplicate values.
.It Ic sort(.field)
Sort by field.
.It Ic group(.field)
Group into a record keyed by field value.
.El
.Ss Record Operations
.Bl -tag -width "has(name)" -compact
.It Ic keys
List record keys.
.It Ic has(name)
Check if a field exists.
.El
.Ss Format Conversion
.Bl -tag -width "yaml" -compact
.It Ic yaml
Record to YAML text, or YAML text to record.
.It Ic toml
Record to TOML text, or TOML text to record.
.El
.Ss Mutation
.Bl -tag -width "set(.field, value)" -compact
.It Ic set(.field, value)
Set a frontmatter field. Produces the modified document.
.It Ic del(.field)
Delete a frontmatter field. Produces the modified document.
.It Ic .field += [values]
Append values to a frontmatter array field.
Produces the modified document.
If the field is null, creates it with the given array.
If the field is an array, concatenates the values.
.El
.Ss Link Validation
.Bl -tag -width "resolve" -compact
.It Ic exists
Add
.Li .exists
boolean to link records.
.It Ic resolve
Add
.Li .path
with the resolved filesystem path.
.El
.Ss Comma Operator
Multiple outputs from the same input:
.Li "(.title, .draft)" .
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -json
Output in JSON format.
.It Fl -dir Ar directory
Directory for
.Ic incoming ,
.Ic exists ,
and
.Ic resolve .
.It Fl i
Edit the file in-place. The program must produce a document string.
.It Fl h , Fl -help
Show usage information.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Get a frontmatter field:
.Dl md 'frontmatter | .title' notes.md
.Pp
List h2 headings:
.Dl md 'headings | select(.depth == 2)' notes.md
.Pp
Count wikilinks:
.Dl md 'links | select(.kind == \&"wikilink\&") | count' notes.md
.Pp
Set a frontmatter field in-place:
.Dl md 'frontmatter | set(.draft, false)' -i notes.md
.Pp
Delete a frontmatter field:
.Dl md 'frontmatter | del(.tags)' -i notes.md
.Pp
Extract content under a heading using nodes:
.Dl md 'nodes | skip_until(.text == \&"API\&") | take_until(.type == \&"heading\&")' notes.md
.Pp
Find broken links:
.Dl md 'links | exists | select(.exists == false)' --dir ./vault/ notes.md
.Pp
Find incoming links:
.Dl md 'incoming' --dir ./vault/ notes.md
.Pp
JSON output:
.Dl md 'headings' --json notes.md
.Pp
Append to a frontmatter array:
.Dl md 'frontmatter | .tags += [\&"new-tag\&"]' -i notes.md
.Pp
Extract content between comment markers:
.Dl md 'nodes | skip_until(.type == \&"comment\&" and contains(.text, \&"begin\&")) | take_until(.type == \&"comment\&" and contains(.text, \&"end\&"))' notes.md
.Pp
Read from stdin:
.Dl cat notes.md | md 'tags | map(.name) | unique'
.Pp
Process all files in a vault:
.Dl find vault/ -name '*.md' -exec md 'frontmatter | .title' {} \e;
.Sh SUPPORTED FORMATS
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Standard Markdown links:
.Li [text](url)
.It
Obsidian wikilinks:
.Li [[target]] ,
.Li [[target|alias]]
.It
Image and embed links:
.Li ![alt](url) ,
.Li ![[embed]]
.It
YAML frontmatter (delimited by
.Li --- )
.It
TOML frontmatter (delimited by
.Li +++ )
.It
ATX headings
.Pq Li "# H1"
through
.Li "###### H6"
.It
Fenced code blocks (backtick and tilde)
.It
Indented code blocks (4+ spaces or tab)
.It
Inline tags
.Pq Li #tag
.It
HTML comments
.Pq Li "<!-- ... -->"
.It
Obsidian comments
.Pq Li "%% ... %%"
.It
Footnote definitions
.Pq Li "[^label]: text"
.El
